Company | Smart Glass | Research Frontiers












































































































































Company











Overview Research Frontiers is the developer of SPD-SmartGlass, electronically tintable window technology. Electronically tintable glass developed by Research Frontiers changes the tint of any window, sunroof or skylight by electrically aligning tiny particles in a thin film within the glass or plastic. With the touch of a button, users can instantly change or tune the tint of their glass to help keep out harsh sunlight and 95% of the heat in its tinted (power off) state. Patented SPD-SmartGlass technology effectively blocks UV and infrared rays regardless of whether the glass is in its clear or tinted state, helping keep cars, planes, yachts, homes, offices and artwork cooler and protected.
SPD-SmartGlass is versatile and can be controlled in many ways. For example SPD-SmartGlass can be operated from a wall switch, dimmer, motion detector, light or temperature sensor, Zuli or other smartplug and can be easily integrated into any building control system.
Research Frontiers has invested over $100 million to develop and license out this technology to over 40 companies around the world to serve the global market.
 Executive Team ROBERT L. SAXE
Chairman of the Board, Chief Technology Officer
(In Memorium – June 29, 2016)
  JOSEPH M. HARARY
President and Chief Executive Officer, Director, General Counsel, Corporate Secretary
  SETH L. VAN VOORHEES
Chief Financial Officer, Treasurer, Vice President – Business Development
  MICHAEL R. LAPOINTE
Vice President – Aerospace Products
  STEVEN M. SLOVAK
Vice President – Technology
 Licensees 





Advnanotech LLC
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart architectural window products and skylights, automotive sunroofs, and other automotive window products.
			  








AGC Automotive Americas (f/k/a AP Technoglass Co.)
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart sunroof glass to selected licensees of Research Frontiers.
			  








AGC Flat Glass Europe SA
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart architectural window products and skylights.
			  








American Glass Products (AGP USA)
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart architectural window products and skylights, automotive sunroofs, and other automotive window products.
			  








Avery Dennison
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart information display products.
			  








BRG Group, Ltd.
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart architectural window products and skylights, automotive sunroofs, and other automotive window products.
			  








Craftsman Fabricated Glass, Ltd.
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart laminated glass and plastic to selected licensees of Research Frontiers.
			  








Cricursa Cristales Curvados S.A.
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart architectural window products and skylights, automotive sunroofs, and other automotive window products.
			  








Custom Glass Corporation
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart windows and sunroofs for mass transit trains and busses, and also licensed to sell SPD-Smart laminated glass and plastic to selected licensees of Research Frontiers.
			  








Daimler AG
Licensed to use Research Frontiers’ electronics patents to control SPD-SmartGlass technology in their cars, trucks and other vehicles.
			  








Diamond Glass
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart architectural windows, skylights and partitions throughout Europe.
			  








Diamond Sea-Glaze Manufacturing Ltd.
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart marine window products and marine sunvisor products.
			  








DIC Corporation (formerly known as Dainippon Ink & Chemicals Inc.)
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart film, and emulsion used to make SPD film, to selected licensees of Research Frontiers.
			  








E. I. DuPont de Nemours and Company
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart film, and emulsion used to make SPD film, to selected licensees of Research Frontiers, and also licensed to sell SPD-Smart architectural window products and skylights, automotive sunroofs, and other automotive window products.
			  








Film Technologies International, Inc.
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart film to selected licensees of Research Frontiers.
			  








GKN Aerospace Transparency Systems Inc.
Licensed to sell armored SPD-Smart products including windows, sunroofs, roof panels and other armored transportation vehicle window products, and SPD-Smart products for aircraft.
			  








Global Mirror GmbH & Co. KG, and group of affiliated companies
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart sun visors and rear-view mirrors for cars, trucks, and other commercial vehicles.
			  








Hitachi Chemical Co., Ltd.
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart film, and emulsion used to make SPD film, to selected licensees of Research Frontiers.
			  








Hotel Technologies
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart architectural window products and skylights to the hotel industry.
			  








iGlass Pty Limited
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart film to selected licensees of Research Frontiers, and also licensed to sell SPD-Smart architectural window products and skylights.
			  








Innovative Glass Corporation
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart architectural window products and skylights.
			  








InspecTech Aero Service, Inc.
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart aircraft and marine windows, cabin dividers, sun visors, and windows for certain custom vehicles.
			  








Isoclima S.p.A.
Licensed to sell SPD-Smart film, and emulsion used to make SPD film, to selected licensees of Research Frontiers, and also licensed to sell SPD-Smart aircraft window products, architectural window products and skylights, automotive sunroofs and other automotive window products, and marine window products.
			  








